The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Saturday, August 13, 2005 

 Asim opens DA purse 

 Calcutta, Aug. 12: Finance minister Asim Dasgupta today released an instalment of dearness allowance equivalent to 3 per cent of basic pay for the governments 10-lakh plus employees.

 Teachers and non-teaching staff of government and government-aided educational institutions, employees of government undertakings, local bodies and corporations will also get it with effect from September 1. About 400,000 pensioners will also benefit from the announcement. With this, government employees and pensioners will get 55 per cent of their basic as DA from October. Central employees get 67 per cent. 

 The state will now incur an additional expenditure of Rs 147 crore, Dasgupta said. 




